A new vaccination.
Free vaccines for children in August.
Since January, children born last year from August 2 can be vaccinated for free against pneumococcal disease.
The condition is that they have not yet been vaccinated.
If you started vaccination last year or earlier, you will have to pay for the following vaccinations yourself.
The first dose of vaccine should be given between the 3rd and 5th month of the child.
Last year, a quarter of families voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal disease.
However, parents paid 1,600 crowns or more for a dose.
Vaccination of the youngest requires four doses.
Experts estimate that health insurance companies spend 300 to 450,000 crowns each year on vaccine doses.
However, they save on the medical care that unvaccinated children would need.
So far, the state has spent about 500,000 crowns a year on all vaccination of children.
The reimbursed vaccination was introduced with the "Janota package".
Pneumococci are the cause of inflammation of the middle ear but also serious infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
According to hospital investigations, there are up to 28 deaths of children under the age of 10 caused by pneumococcal infections.
Apart from the Czech Republic, about 40 other countries have introduced the reimbursed vaccination.
Will vaccination be mandatory?
There are opinions about a possible vaccination obligation in the future.
From January, it must be paid by insurance and optional.
For example, the president of the Nahlas Rudolf Kalovsk<0xC3><0xBD> association indicated that a mandatory vaccination would be more positive.
